17 Article – Economic Development
18 10–826.
19 (a) On or before December 1 of each year, the Center shall report to the Governor,
20 the Administration, and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government Article, the
21 General Assembly.
22 (b) The report shall include:
23 (1) a complete operating and financial statement covering the Center’s
24 operations;
25 (2) a summary of the Center’s activities during the preceding fiscal year;
26 [and]
27 (3) a summary of the Center’s activities specific to clean energy innovation;
28 AND
29 (4) A SUMMARY OF THE CENTER’S ACTIVITIES SPECIFIC TO THE
30 GREEN AND RENEWABLE ENERGY EFFICIENCY FOR NONPROFITS LOAN PROGRAM
31 ESTABLISHED UNDER § 10–863 OF THIS SUBTITLE, INCLUDING:
32 (I) THE TOTAL NUMBER OF LOANS AWARDED;

12 HOUSE BILL 1532
1 (II) THE TOTAL MONETARY VALUE OF THE LOANS AWARDED;
2 (III) THE AVERAGE TERM OF LOANS IN THE LOAN PORTFOLIO;
3 (IV) THE ESTIMATED ANNUAL ENERGY SAVINGS, IN
4 KILOWATT–HOURS, RESULTING FROM MEASURES ASSOCIATED WITH LOANS IN THE
5 LOAN PORTFOLIO; AND
6 (V) THE ESTIMATED REDUCTION OF GREENHOUSE GAS
7 EMISSIONS, IN METRIC TONS, ASSOCIATED WITH LOANS IN THE LOAN PORTFOLIO.
8 PART VII. GREEN AND RENEWABLE ENERGY EFFICIENCY FOR NONPROFITS LOAN
9 PROGRAM.
10 10–862.
11 (A) IN THIS PART THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS INDICATED.
12 (B) “BORROWER” MEANS A NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION THAT APPLIES AND
13 QUALIFIES FOR A LOAN UNDER THE PROGRAM.
14 (C) “FUND” MEANS THE GREEN AND RENEWABLE ENERGY EFFICIENCY FOR
15 NONPROFITS LOAN FUND.
16 (D) “NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION” MEANS AN ORGANIZATION THAT IS
17 EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAX UNDER § 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL
18 REVENUE CODE.
19 (E) “PROGRAM” MEANS THE GREEN AND RENEWABLE ENERGY EFFICIENCY
20 FOR NONPROFITS LOAN PROGRAM.
21 (F) “QUALIFYING ENERGY SYSTEM” MEANS A SYSTEM THAT:
22 (1) GENERATES ELECTRICITY OR USABLE THERMAL ENERGY THAT IS
23 USED TO MEET ON–SITE DEMAND; AND
24 (2) ASSISTS THE STATE IN MEETING THE ENVIRONMENTAL AND
25 GREENHOUSE GAS REDUCTION GOALS UNDER TITLE 2, SUBTITLE 12 OF THE
26 ENVIRONMENT ARTICLE.
27 10–863.

HOUSE BILL 1532 13
1 THERE IS A GREEN AND RENEWABLE ENERGY EFFICIENCY FOR NONPROFITS
2 LOAN PROGRAM IN THE CENTER.
3 10–864.
4 THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS TO PROVIDE FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE IN
5 THE FORM OF NO–INTEREST LOANS TO NONPROFIT ORGANIZATIONS FOR:
6 (1) THE PLANNING, PURCHASE, AND INSTALLATION OF QUALIFYING
7 ENERGY SYSTEMS IN THE STATE; AND
8 (2) ACTIONS THAT IMPROVE ENERGY EFFICIENCY, SUCH AS
9 REPAIRING OR REPLACING WINDOWS, DOORS, AND HEATING, VENTILATION, AND
10 AIR–CONDITIONING SYSTEMS AND OTHER SIMILAR IMPROVEMENTS.
11 10–865.
12 THE CENTER SHALL:
13 (1) MANAGE, SUPERVISE, AND ADMINISTER THE PROGRAM;
14 (2) ADOPT REGULATIONS TO ENSURE THAT LOANS PROVIDED TO
15 NONPROFIT ORGANIZATIONS CARRY OUT THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM; AND
16 (3) ATTACH TO ANY LOAN SPECIFIC TERMS THAT ARE CONSIDERED
17 NECESSARY TO ENSURE THAT THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS FULFILLED.
18 10–866.
19 (A) (1) A BORROWER MUST FILE AN APPLICATION WITH THE CENTER TO
20 RECEIVE A LOAN UNDER THE PROGRAM.
21 (2) THE APPLICATION MUST BE SIGNED BY THE CHIEF OPERATING
22 OFFICER OR AN AUTHORIZED OFFICER OF THE NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION.
23 (B) THE APPLICATION MUST CONTAIN ANY INFORMATION THE CENTER
24 DETERMINES IS NECESSARY, INCLUDING:
25 (1) THE PROJECTED COST OF THE QUALIFYING ENERGY SYSTEM,
26 ENERGY EFFICIENCY ACTION, OR TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE BEING FINANCED
27 THROUGH THE LOAN;

14 HOUSE BILL 1532
1 (2) THE LOCATION OF THE PROPERTY WHERE THE QUALIFYING
2 ENERGY SYSTEM WILL BE INSTALLED OR AN ENERGY EFFICIENCY ACTION WILL
3 OCCUR AND WHETHER THE PROPERTY IS OWNED OR LEASED BY THE APPLICANT;
4 (3) (I) EVIDENCE THAT THE BORROWER:
5 1. IS CURRENT ON ITS REGISTRATION STATUS WITH THE
6 SECRETARY OF STATE AT THE TIME THE BORROWER SUBMITS THE APPLICATION; OR
7 2. IS AN EXEMPT ORGANIZATION THAT IS COMPLYING
8 WITH ANY FILING REQUIREMENTS OF THE SECRETARY OF STATE RELATED TO
9 EXEMPT ORGANIZATIONS; OR
10 (II) CERTIFICATION THAT THE BORROWER IS NOT REQUIRED TO
11 REGISTER OR FILE AS AN EXEMPT ORGANIZATION WITH THE SECRETARY OF STATE
12 BECAUSE THE BORROWER DOES NOT SOLICIT CHARITABLE CONTRIBUTIONS IN THE
13 STATE; AND
14 (4) ANY ADDITIONAL INFORMATION RELATING TO THE BORROWER OR
15 THE PROPOSED QUALIFYING ENERGY SYSTEM OR ENERGY EFFICIENCY ACTION
16 BEING FINANCED THROUGH THE LOAN THAT MAY BE REQUIRED BY THE CENTER TO
17 ADMINISTER THE PROGRAM.
18 (C) THE CENTER MAY APPROVE AN APPLICATION FOR A LOAN SPECIFIED IN
19 § 10–867(A)(1) OR (3) OF THIS SUBTITLE ONLY IF THE APPLICATION DEMONSTRATES
20 THAT THE PROPOSED QUALIFYING ENERGY SYSTEM OR ENERGY EFFICIENCY ACTION
21 IS ESTIMATED, BASED ON PROJECTED ENERGY COSTS, TO GENERATE ENERGY COST
22 SAVINGS OVER THE USEFUL LIFE OF THE SYSTEM OR ENERGY EFFICIENCY ACTION
23 THAT EQUAL OR EXCEED THE TOTAL AMORTIZED COST OF THE LOAN.
