17 (c) (1) Subject to the approval of the Commission, a utility company shall adopt
18 a limited–income mechanism to benefit an eligible limited–income customer.
19 (2) Notwithstanding § 4–503(b) of this title, the mechanism may take the
20 form of a program, tariff provision, credit, rate, rider, or other means to assist an eligible
21 limited–income customer to afford a utility service.
