26 Commission approval under subsection (c) of this section shall include the proposal in:
27 (i) a separate application for approval of the mechanism; or
28 (ii) only with the prior approval of the Commission, an application
29 for a base rate proceeding, including an alternative rate proceeding, or any other proceeding
30 to alter the utility company’s base rates under the authority of the Commission.
31 (2) A proposal submitted under this section shall allocate the prudently
32 incurred costs of the limited–income mechanism across rate classes.

HOUSE BILL 1532 39
1 (3) The proposal shall include:
2 (i) a detailed description of the proposed mechanism;
3 (ii) the proposed method for allocating the mechanism’s costs across
4 customer classes;
5 (iii) the rationale supporting the utility company’s proposal for a
6 mechanism to benefit the eligible limited–income customers in the utility company’s service
7 territory;
8 (iv) a time frame and process for the Commission to review the
9 effectiveness of the mechanism after implementation; and
10 (v) any other information the Commission considers necessary or
11 useful to evaluate the proposal.
12 (e) In evaluating a limited–income mechanism, the Commission shall consider:
13 (1) the degree to which the mechanism promotes affordability of electricity
14 or natural gas for limited–income customers;
15 (2) the public interest in allocating the costs of the mechanism between the
16 utility company’s shareholders and rate payers;
17 (3) the impact on rates, utility operating costs, customer arrearages,
18 customer disconnections, uncollectible costs, and successful completion of payment plans;
19 (4) the ability of a limited–income customer to continue to receive benefits
20 when relocating within the same service territory;
21 (5) coordination of benefits under the mechanism with any other public or
22 private assistance that may be available to the customer;
23 (6) a minimum level of support or assistance structure to provide equitable
24 availability of limited–income assistance across the State; and
25 (7) any other information the Commission considers appropriate.
