1 (c) (1) The Commission shall establish the Maryland Energy Storage Program.
2 (2) The Program shall be implemented no later than July 1, 2025.
3 (3) The Program shall include competitive procurement mechanisms to
4 reach a minimum of 3,000 megawatts of energy storage, or the maximum cost–effective
5 amount of energy storage that can be deployed, by the end of delivery year 2033.
6 (4) The Program may include:
7 (i) a system of energy storage credits and market–based incentives
8 designed to:
9 1. develop a robust energy storage market in the State; and
10 2. deploy energy storage devices in a cost–effective manner;
11 (ii) a requirement that investor–owned electric companies:
12 1. install or contract for energy storage devices; or
13 2. contract for credits from an energy storage project under §
14 7–216 of this subtitle;
15 (iii) a requirement that Program participants make reasonable efforts
16 to apply for all applicable State and federal grants, rebates, tax credits, loan guarantees,
17 and other similar benefits as the benefits become available; or
18 (iv) any other mechanism or policy that the Commission determines
19 is appropriate to achieve the goal of a robust, cost–effective energy storage system in the
20 State.
