7 (I) HAS OR IS PROJECTED TO HAVE AN AGGREGATE MONTHLY
8 DEMAND OF AT LEAST 25 MEGAWATTS; AND
9 (II) HAS OR IS PROJECTED TO HAVE A LOAD FACTOR OF MORE
10 THAN 60%.
11 (2) “LARGE LOAD CUSTOMER” DOES NOT INCLUDE A COMMERCIAL OR
12 INDUSTRIAL CUSTOMER FOR RETAIL ELECTRIC SERVICE WHOSE PRIMARY PURPOSE
13 IS TO OPERATE AS:
14 (I) A WATER COMPANY OR SEWAGE DISPOSAL COMPANY;
15 (II) A MANUFACTURING FACILITY;
16 (III) A HOSPITAL;
17 (IV) A DISTRICT ENERGY SYSTEM;
18 (V) AN AGRICULTURAL FACILITY; OR
19 (VI) AT THE DISCRETION OF THE COMMISSION, ANOTHER
20 INDUSTRIAL FACILITY.
21 (F) “MANUFACTURING FACILITY” MEANS A FACILITY WHERE THE PROCESS
22 OF SUBSTANTIALLY TRANSFORMING, OR A SUBSTANTIAL STEP IN THE PROCESS OF
23 SUBSTANTIALLY TRANSFORMING, TANGIBLE PERSONAL PROPERTY INTO A NEW AND
24 DIFFERENT ARTICLE OF TANGIBLE PERSONAL PROPERTY BY THE USE OF LABOR OR
25 MACHINERY OCCURS.
26 (G) “ON–SITE BACKUP GENERATING FACILITY” MEANS A GENERATING
27 FACILITY THAT IS NOT CONNECTED TO THE ELECTRIC SYSTEM.
28 (H) “VIRTUAL POWER PLANT” MEANS AN AGGREGATION OF DISTRIBUTED
29 CLEAN ENERGY RESOURCES AND ENERGY STORAGE OWNED BY A CUSTOMER OR A
30 THIRD PARTY THAT:

74 HOUSE BILL 1532
1 (1) PROVIDES ELECTRIC SYSTEM SERVICES; AND
2 (2) MAY BE USED BY THE CUSTOMER OR THE THIRD PARTY FOR OTHER
3 APPLICATIONS WHEN NOT PROVIDING ELECTRIC SYSTEM SERVICES.
4 (I) “VOLUNTARY CLEAN CAPACITY RATING PROGRAM” MEANS THE
5 PROGRAM DEVELOPED BY THE COMMISSION UNDER § 7–234 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
6 7–233.
