24 7–321.
25 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “PORTABLE SOLAR ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM”
26 MEANS A MOVABLE PHOTOVOLTAIC SOLAR ENERGY GENERATION DEVICE THAT IS:
27 (1) DESIGNED TO BE CONNECTED TO A BUILDING’S ELECTRICAL
28 SYSTEM THROUGH A STANDARD ELECTRICAL OUTLET;

HOUSE BILL 1532 85
1 (2) PRIMARILY INTENDED TO OFFSET PART OF THE BUILDING’S
2 ELECTRICITY CONSUMPTION;
3 (3) LIMITED TO SUPPLYING A MAXIMUM POWER OUTPUT OF NOT MORE
4 THAN 1,200 WATTS BACK TO THE ELECTRIC SYSTEM OF THE BUILDING; AND
5 (4) CERTIFIED BY UNDERWRITERS LABORATORY OR AN EQUIVALENT
6 NATIONALLY RECOGNIZED TESTING LABORATORY.
7 (B) A PERSON MAY PURCHASE AND INSTALL NOT MORE THAN ONE
8 PORTABLE SOLAR ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM PER ELECTRIC METER FOR
9 RESIDENTIAL USE ONLY.
10 (C) A PORTABLE SOLAR ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM:
11 (1) IS NOT SUBJECT TO THE REQUIREMENTS OF §§ 7–306 AND 7–306.1
12 OF THIS SUBTITLE;
13 (2) IS NOT ELIGIBLE FOR INCLUSION IN MEETING THE RENEWABLE
14 ENERGY PORTFOLIO STANDARD; AND
15 (3) MAY NOT GENERATE RENEWABLE ENERGY CREDITS OF ANY TYPE.
16 (D) AN ELECTRIC COMPANY:
17 (1) MAY NOT REQUIRE A CUSTOMER USING A PORTABLE SOLAR
18 ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM TO:
19 (I) OBTAIN THE ELECTRIC COMPANY’S APPROVAL BEFORE
20 INSTALLING OR USING THE PORTABLE SOLAR ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM;
21 (II) PAY ANY FEE OR CHARGE RELATED TO THE PORTABLE SOLAR
22 ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM’S ABILITY TO FEED ELECTRICITY BACK INTO THE
23 ELECTRIC SYSTEM; OR
24 (III) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBSECTION (E) OF THIS SECTION,
25 INSTALL ANY ADDITIONAL CONTROLS OR EQUIPMENT BEYOND WHAT IS INTEGRATED
26 INTO THE PORTABLE SOLAR ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM; AND
27 (2) IS NOT LIABLE FOR ANY DAMAGE CAUSED BY A PORTABLE SOLAR
28 ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM.
29 (E) A CUSTOMER USING A PORTABLE SOLAR ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM
30 SHALL:

86 HOUSE BILL 1532
1 (1) NOTIFY THE ELECTRIC COMPANY PROVIDING SERVICE IN THE
2 SERVICE TERRITORY IN WHICH THE GENERATING SYSTEM WILL BE INSTALLED
3 BEFORE INSTALLATION;
4 (2) PROVIDE TO THE ELECTRIC COMPANY PROVIDING SERVICE IN THE
5 SERVICE TERRITORY IN WHICH THE GENERATING SYSTEM WILL BE OR IS INSTALLED
6 A CERTIFICATION OF THE SAFETY FEATURES AND MAXIMUM GENERATING CAPACITY
7 OF THE GENERATING SYSTEM; AND
8 (3) IF THE GENERATING SYSTEM REQUIRES AN AUTOMATIC LOCKING
9 DISCONNECT SWITCH TO BE INSTALLED, PAY FOR THE SWITCH INSTALLATION.
10 (F) A PORTABLE SOLAR ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM THAT HAS A
11 MAXIMUM POWER OUTPUT TO A STANDARD ELECTRICAL OUTLET OF NOT MORE THAN
12 391 WATTS IS EXEMPT FROM PRODUCT LISTING PROVISIONS FROM UNDERWRITERS
