15 SUBTITLE 20E. ALTERNATIVE COMPLIANCE FEE AUCTIONS.
16 9–20E–01.
17 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
18 INDICATED.
19 (B) “ADMINISTRATION” MEANS THE MARYLAND ENERGY ADMINISTRATION.
20 (C) “ALTERNATIVE COMPLIANCE FEE” MEANS A FEE PAID IN ACCORDANCE
21 WITH § 7–705 OF THE PUBLIC UTILITIES ARTICLE TO THE MARYLAND STRATEGIC
22 ENERGY INVESTMENT FUND ESTABLISHED UNDER § 9–20B–05 OF THIS TITLE.
23 (D) “AUCTION” MEANS AN ALTERNATIVE COMPLIANCE FEE AUCTION.
24 (E) “CAPACITY TARGET” MEANS THE LESSER OF:
25 (1) THE CALCULATION OF THE AMOUNT OF RENEWABLE ENERGY
26 GENERATION NEEDED IN A GIVEN YEAR TO SATISFY THE RENEWABLE ENERGY
27 PORTFOLIO STANDARD UNDER § 7–703 OF THE PUBLIC UTILITIES ARTICLE FOR A
28 SPECIFIC YEAR, MINUS THE AMOUNT ALREADY PROCURED FROM OTHER SOURCES;
29 OR
30 (2) THE AMOUNT OF RENEWABLE ENERGY THAT CAN BE PROCURED
31 USING ALTERNATIVE COMPLIANCE FEES AVAILABLE FOR THE AUCTION.

HOUSE BILL 1532 109
1 (F) “COMMISSION” MEANS THE PUBLIC SERVICE COMMISSION.
2 (G) “RENEWABLE ENERGY” MEANS:
3 (1) ENERGY GENERATED FROM:
4 (I) A TIER 1 RENEWABLE SOURCE THAT DOES NOT PARTICIPATE
5 IN NET ENERGY METERING UNDER § 7–306, § 7–306.2, § 7–306.3, OR § 7–306.4 OF
6 THE PUBLIC UTILITIES ARTICLE;
7 (II) A TIER 1 RENEWABLE SOURCE THAT:
8 1. MEETS THE REQUIREMENTS OF ITEM (I) OF THIS
9 PARAGRAPH; AND
10 2. INCLUDES A CO–LOCATED ENERGY STORAGE DEVICE;
11 OR
12 (III) AN ENERGY STORAGE DEVICE THAT IS PLANNED TO BE
13 CO–LOCATED WITH A TIER 1 RENEWABLE SOURCE; OR
14 (2) ENERGY FROM AN ENERGY STORAGE DEVICE THAT IS NOT
15 PLANNED TO BE CO–LOCATED WITH A TIER 1 RENEWABLE SOURCE.
16 (H) “TIER 1 RENEWABLE SOURCE” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 7–701 OF
17 THE PUBLIC UTILITIES ARTICLE.
18 9–20E–02.
19 (A) FOR 2027 AND 2028, THE ADMINISTRATION SHALL CONDUCT, IN
20 CONSULTATION WITH THE COMMISSION, AN ANNUAL, COMPETITIVE, ALTERNATIVE
21 COMPLIANCE FEE AUCTION TO AWARD GRANTS TO ELIGIBLE BIDDERS TO OFFSET A
22 PORTION OF PROJECT COSTS ASSOCIATED WITH THE DEVELOPMENT OF RENEWABLE
23 ENERGY IN THE STATE USING REVENUE FROM ALTERNATIVE COMPLIANCE FEES.
24 (B) (1) THE ADMINISTRATION, IN CONSULTATION WITH THE
25 COMMISSION, SHALL DEVELOP AND CONDUCT THE AUCTIONS IN A MANNER THAT IS
26 COST–EFFECTIVE AND MAINTAINS AND PROMOTES THE DEVELOPMENT OF
27 RENEWABLE ENERGY IN THE STATE.
28 (2) THE COMPETITIVE AUCTION PROCESS MAY REQUIRE THE
29 ADMINISTRATION TO SOLICIT A SERIES OF BIDS FROM RENEWABLE ENERGY
30 PROJECT DEVELOPERS FOR THE DEVELOPMENT OF RENEWABLE ENERGY PROJECTS
31 IN A COST–EFFECTIVE MANNER.

110 HOUSE BILL 1532
1 (C) (1) TO BE ELIGIBLE TO SUBMIT A BID UNDER THIS SECTION, A PERSON
2 MUST:
3 (I) BE A RENEWABLE ENERGY PROJECT DEVELOPER; AND
4 (II) MEET THE MINIMUM CREDIT AND OTHER ELIGIBILITY
5 REQUIREMENTS SET UNDER PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
6 (2) THE ADMINISTRATION, IN CONSULTATION WITH THE
7 COMMISSION, SHALL SET ELIGIBILITY REQUIREMENTS FOR BIDDERS, INCLUDING
8 REQUIRING EACH BIDDER TO:
9 (I) PROVIDE PROOF OF FINANCIAL INTEGRITY;
10 (II) POST A BOND OR OTHER SIMILAR INSTRUMENT;
11 (III) AGREE TO BE SUBJECT TO ALL APPLICABLE TAXES AND
12 FEES;
13 (IV) DEMONSTRATE THE ABILITY TO FINANCE, EXECUTE, AND
14 COMMISSION PROJECTS;
15 (V) PROVIDE, IN ACCORDANCE WITH PARAGRAPH (3) OF THIS
16 SUBSECTION, EVIDENCE THAT IS SATISFACTORY TO THE ADMINISTRATION THAT
17 AWARDED FUNDS ARE NECESSARY FOR THE RENEWABLE ENERGY PROJECT TO BE
18 CONSTRUCTED; AND
19 (VI) COMPLY WITH ANY OTHER REQUIREMENTS THE
20 ADMINISTRATION DETERMINES ARE IN THE PUBLIC INTEREST.
21 (3) THE EVIDENCE PROVIDED UNDER PARAGRAPH (2)(V) OF THIS
22 SUBSECTION SHALL BE PROVIDED TO THE ADMINISTRATION AND MAINTAINED BY
23 THE ADMINISTRATION IN A MANNER THAT KEEPS THE EVIDENCE CONFIDENTIAL.
24 (D) (1) ELIGIBLE BIDDERS SHALL SUBMIT COMPETITIVE BIDS BY
25 SPECIFYING:
26 (I) THE ACTUAL AMOUNT OF MEGAWATTS TO BE GENERATED BY
27 THE RENEWABLE ENERGY PROJECT;
28 (II) A PRICE PER MEGAWATT THAT WOULD BE REQUIRED FROM
29 THE AUCTION; AND

HOUSE BILL 1532 111
1 (III) ANY OTHER INFORMATION THE ADMINISTRATION
2 DETERMINES IS NECESSARY.
3 (2) (I) SUBJECT TO SUBPARAGRAPH (II) OF THIS PARAGRAPH, THE
4 ADMINISTRATION SHALL RANK BIDS FROM LOWEST TO HIGHEST COST PER
5 MEGAWATT AND AWARD FUNDS DERIVED FROM ALTERNATIVE COMPLIANCE FEES TO
6 THE LOWEST BID OR BIDS.
7 (II) THE ADMINISTRATION SHALL PRIORITIZE BIDS FOR
8 RENEWABLE ENERGY PROJECTS SPECIFIED IN § 9–20E–01(G)(1) OF THIS SUBTITLE.
9 (3) (I) SUBJECT TO SUBPARAGRAPH (II) OF THIS PARAGRAPH, THE
10 ADMINISTRATION SHALL AWARD BIDS UNTIL THE CAPACITY TARGET IS REACHED.
11 (II) THE ADMINISTRATION MAY REFUSE TO ACCEPT SOME OR
12 ALL OF THE BIDS MADE IN A COMPETITIVE AUCTION IN ACCORDANCE WITH
13 STANDARDS ADOPTED BY THE ADMINISTRATION.
14 (4) (I) IF THE CAPACITY TARGET CAN BE MET AT A COST BELOW THE
15 ALLOCATED FUNDING, THE ADMINISTRATION MAY:
16 1. CARRY FORWARD ANY FUNDING TO THE NEXT
17 AUCTION, IF APPLICABLE; OR
18 2. APPLY THE FUNDS FOR ANY ADDITIONAL MEGAWATTS
19 OF RENEWABLE ENERGY THAT HAVE BEEN OFFERED UNDER THE AUCTION.
20 (II) ANY AMOUNT OF ALLOCATED FUNDING THAT IS NOT
21 CARRIED FORWARD OR APPLIED UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF THIS PARAGRAPH
22 SHALL ACCRUE IN THE MARYLAND STRATEGIC ENERGY INVESTMENT FUND AND
23 MAY BE ALLOCATED FOR ANY PURPOSE FOR WHICH ALTERNATIVE COMPLIANCE FEE
24 REVENUE IS AUTHORIZED TO BE USED.
25 (E) (1) THE ADMINISTRATION SHALL SET DELIVERY DEADLINES FOR
26 EACH RENEWABLE ENERGY PROJECT THAT IS AWARDED FUNDING FROM AN
27 AUCTION.
28 (2) THE DEADLINES SET IN PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION
29 SHALL INCLUDE MILESTONES THAT REQUIRE THE DEVELOPER TO MEET CERTAIN
30 DELIVERY GOALS DURING THE DEVELOPMENT OF A RENEWABLE ENERGY PROJECT.
31 (3) THE ADMINISTRATION MAY GRANT EXTENSIONS FOR DELIVERY
32 GOALS THAT ARE DELAYED DUE TO INTERCONNECTION OR PERMITTING

112 HOUSE BILL 1532
1 CHALLENGES OR DELAYS IF THE DEVELOPER PROVIDES DOCUMENTATION OF THE
2 CHALLENGE OR DELAY.
3 (4) THE ADMINISTRATION SHALL ESTABLISH A METHOD OF
4 COLLECTION AGAINST ANY DEVELOPER AWARDED A GRANT UNDER THIS SECTION TO
5 RECAPTURE ANY FUNDS RECEIVED AS A RESULT OF:
6 (I) MISAPPROPRIATION, OVERPAYMENT, OR FRAUD; OR
7 (II) FAILURE TO MEET MILESTONES OR DELIVERY DATES.
8 (F) WITHIN 90 DAYS AFTER ALL GRANTS FOR RENEWABLE ENERGY
9 PROJECTS ARE EXECUTED, THE ADMINISTRATION SHALL PUBLICLY DISCLOSE THE
10 NAMES OF EACH SUCCESSFUL BIDDER AND THE MEGAWATTS TO BE DELIVERED BY
11 THE DEVELOPMENT OF THE RENEWABLE ENERGY PROJECT.
