24 per megawatt and other benefits identified in a cost–benefit analysis, but not including any
25 anticipated wholesale energy and ancillary services revenue;
26 (2) include a cost–benefit analysis of the project and proposed pricing
27 schedule comparison on a dollar–per–megawatt–hour basis, including an analysis of:
28 (i) the locational value and time to deployment of the energy storage
29 devices;
30 (ii) the value of long–duration storage, including its capacity
31 accreditation value for resource adequacy as measured in PJM Interconnection’s effective
32 load carrying capability class ratings;

