1 (iii) avoided or delayed transmission, generation, and distribution
2 costs;
3 (iv) avoided emissions in the short term and projected avoided
4 emissions in the long term, measured using the social cost of carbon, as determined by the
5 U.S. Environmental Protection Agency as of January 1, 2025;
6 (v) the value of the rapid deployment of energy storage devices;
7 (vi) the value of reliability during periods of electric system stress,
8 including the ability to deliver capacity during periods of extreme weather, fuel scarcity, and
9 large unplanned resource outages; and
10 (vii) any other avoided costs;
11 (3) ensure that the owner or operator of the project has the capability to
