5 (2) “Contract capacity” means the amount of monthly peak load
6 requirements:
7 (i) that is mutually agreed to by an electric company and a large
8 load customer for each month remaining in a contract term after the load ramp period has
9 ended; and
10 (ii) for which:
11 1. the electric company agrees to provide all of the
12 components of retail electric service subject to the terms and conditions in its tariffs; and
13 2. the large load customer agrees to purchase service at that
14 load level for the stated term of the contract and under the same terms and conditions as
