16 (3) “Large load customer” means a commercial or industrial customer for
17 retail electric service that:
18 (i) has or is projected to have an aggregate monthly demand of at
19 least [100] 25 megawatts; and
20 (ii) has or is projected to have a load factor of over [80%] 75%.
21 (4) “Load ramp period” means the period of time from commencement of
22 service until a large load customer’s billing calculation is based on the full contract capacity.
23 (b) It is the intent of the General Assembly that residential retail electric
24 customers in the State should not bear the financial risks associated with large load
25 customers interconnecting to the electric system serving the State.
26 (c) (1) (i) On or before September 1, 2026, each investor–owned electric
27 company and each electric cooperative shall submit to the Commission for approval a
28 specific rate schedule for large load customers that accomplishes the intent of subsection
29 (b) of this section.
