15 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “PORTABLE SOLAR ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM”
16 MEANS A MOVABLE PHOTOVOLTAIC SOLAR ENERGY GENERATION DEVICE THAT IS:
17 (1) DESIGNED TO BE CONNECTED TO A BUILDING’S ELECTRICAL
18 SYSTEM THROUGH A STANDARD ELECTRICAL OUTLET;
19 (2) PRIMARILY INTENDED TO OFFSET PART OF THE BUILDING’S
20 ELECTRICITY CONSUMPTION;
21 (3) LIMITED TO SUPPLYING A MAXIMUM POWER OUTPUT OF NOT
22 MORE THAN 391 WATTS BACK TO THE ELECTRIC SYSTEM OF THE BUILDING; AND
23 (4) CERTIFIED BY UNDERWRITERS LABORATORY OR AN EQUIVALENT
24 NATIONALLY RECOGNIZED TESTING LABORATORY.
25 (B) A PERSON MAY PURCHASE AND INSTALL NOT MORE THAN ONE
26 PORTABLE SOLAR ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM PER ELECTRIC METER FOR
27 RESIDENTIAL USE ONLY.
28 (C) A PORTABLE SOLAR ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM:
29 (1) IS NOT SUBJECT TO THE REQUIREMENTS OF §§ 7–306 AND 7–306.1
30 OF THIS SUBTITLE;

194 HOUSE BILL 1532
1 (2) IS NOT ELIGIBLE FOR INCLUSION IN MEETING THE RENEWABLE
2 ENERGY PORTFOLIO STANDARD; AND
3 (3) MAY NOT GENERATE RENEWABLE ENERGY CREDITS OF ANY TYPE.
4 (D) AN ELECTRIC COMPANY:
5 (1) MAY NOT REQUIRE A CUSTOMER USING A PORTABLE SOLAR
6 ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM TO:
7 (I) OBTAIN THE ELECTRIC COMPANY’S APPROVAL BEFORE
8 INSTALLING OR USING THE PORTABLE SOLAR ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM;
9 (II) PAY ANY FEE OR CHARGE RELATED TO THE PORTABLE
10 SOLAR ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM’S ABILITY TO FEED ELECTRICITY BACK INTO
11 THE ELECTRIC SYSTEM; OR
12 (III) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBSECTION (E) OF THIS SECTION,
13 INSTALL ANY ADDITIONAL CONTROLS OR EQUIPMENT BEYOND WHAT IS
14 INTEGRATED INTO THE PORTABLE SOLAR ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM; AND
15 (2) IS NOT LIABLE FOR ANY DAMAGE CAUSED BY A PORTABLE SOLAR
16 ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM.
17 (E) A CUSTOMER USING A PORTABLE SOLAR ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM
18 SHALL:
19 (1) NOTIFY THE ELECTRIC COMPANY PROVIDING SERVICE IN THE
20 SERVICE TERRITORY IN WHICH THE GENERATING SYSTEM WILL BE INSTALLED ONCE
21 THE GENERATING SYSTEM IS INSTALLED;
22 (2) PROVIDE TO THE ELECTRIC COMPANY PROVIDING SERVICE IN
23 THE SERVICE TERRITORY IN WHICH THE GENERATING SYSTEM WILL BE OR IS
24 INSTALLED A CERTIFICATION OF THE SAFETY FEATURES AND MAXIMUM
25 GENERATING CAPACITY OF THE GENERATING SYSTEM; AND
26 (3) IF THE GENERATING SYSTEM REQUIRES AN AUTOMATIC LOCKING
27 DISCONNECT SWITCH TO BE INSTALLED, PAY FOR THE SWITCH INSTALLATION.
